Esoteric lift bros, do any of you do standing overhead barbell triceps extension/freedom press and how much weight do you load/how does it compare to your overhead press numbers? Been testing it out after seeing young pre-skittles Dr. Mike Israel push 2 plates for 8 reps on it...

It's like behind the neck press but you're pushing with your triceps instead of shoulders, obviously far less isolation than cable stuff or ez-bar French presses, sorta like a standing JM press, we need to figure out a real name for it but pls share ur experiences...
Very interesting, do you just throw them after OHP etc. or do you see them as a real compound to focus on?
I think Bugenhagen said you can wear a baseball hat backwards and try to touch the bill on every rep or something similar for tactile feedback
I generally like doing all my lifts standing, easier to do a few cheat reps at the end of a set hehe

From what I have heard pharmaceutical advertisements on TV are actually a way for pharma companies to "lobby" media and basically pay them money and in return it's expected media companies won't amplify news about some drug giving people cancer, will give them only good coverage.
Like the advertisements themselves are not that important but pharma giving the money to mass media acts as a legal bribe and both parties understand it this way.
To be honest you'd be surprised how many patients need to be told stuff like this
